---
const stats = [
  { label: "Players", value: "Up to 5" },
  { label: "Network", value: "LAN + tunnel" },
  { label: "Levels", value: "10 procedural" },
  { label: "Platform", value: "Windows" },
];
---

<section id="about" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
  <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_1fr] gap-12 items-center">
    <div>
      <p
        class="chip-pixel bg-[color:var(--color-gold)] text-[color:var(--color-ink)] mb-4"
        style="font-family: var(--font-display);"
      >
        ※ About
      </p>
      <h2 class="heading-pixel text-3xl sm:text-4xl">What is Skyward Race?</h2>
      <p
        class="mt-5 text-[color:var(--color-sky-light)] leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base"
        style="font-family: var(--font-body);"
      >
        A 2D pixel-art racer where up to five players climb procedurally
        generated towers, dodge each other, and grab buff/debuff orbs along
        the way. Built as the final project for CS323 &mdash; Parallel and
        Distributed Computing &mdash; the game's heart is real-time
        server-authoritative UDP networking with rooms, ready-ups, and
        post-match results.
      </p>
      <p
        class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-sky-light)] leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base"
        style="font-family: var(--font-body);"
      >
        Currently <strong>LAN-only</strong> &mdash; play over a local network,
        or expose your room to friends with a tunneling service like <a
          href="https://playit.gg"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)] hover:text-[color:var(--color-crown)] underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4"
          >playit.gg</a
        > and direct-join via host:port.
      </p>
      <p
        class="mt-4 text-[color:var(--color-sky-light)] leading-relaxed text-sm sm:text-base"
        style="font-family: var(--font-body);"
      >
        A Godot 4.6 port is in progress &mdash; track it on the <a
          href="/roadmap"
          class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)] hover:text-[color:var(--color-crown)] underline decoration-2 underline-offset-4"
          >roadmap</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
      {
        stats.map((s) => (
          <div class="panel-pixel p-4">
            <dt
              class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-muted)]"
              style="font-family: var(--font-display);"
            >
              {s.label}
            </dt>
            <dd
              class="mt-2 text-base font-bold text-[color:var(--color-gold)]"
              style="font-family: var(--font-display);"
            >
              {s.value}
            </dd>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>
